                question: "List the three main clinical findings that form the triad of Graves Disease.",
                answer: "1) Hyperthyroidism due to hyperfunctional, diffuse enlargement of the thyroid, 2) Infiltrative ophthalmopathy with resultant exophthalmos, and 3) Localized, infiltrative dermopathy (pretibial myxedema)."
