                answer: "Mean age of presentation is 65 years. Half of patients have a history of multinodular goiter, and 20-30% have a concurrent differentiated thyroid tumor (often papillary carcinoma)."
            },
            {
                question: "List two common gross features of Anaplastic Carcinoma.",
                answer: "Huge white or tan mass, oftentimes invading adjacent structures. Necrosis and hemorrhages are commonly seen."
            },
            {
                question: "What are the common histological patterns of Anaplastic Thyroid Carcinoma?",
                answer: "Large, pleomorphic giant cells (including osteoclast-like multinucleate giant cells); spindle cells with a sarcomatous appearance; mixed spindle and giant cells; and small cells resembling those seen in small cell carcinomas arising at other sites."
